  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Somont is run by the lovely Rudiferia family and we know you’ll have a great stay here. They work tirelessly to create a welcoming atmosphere and the hotel's been beautifully maintained.</p>
<h2>Relaxing in the spa</h2>
<p>It’s a great space with a heated indoor pool, whirlpool with colour therapy lights and a lot of saunas. There’s a traditional Finnish sauna, Bio sauna, Infra-red aromatherapy sauna and a Turkish steam bath. It couldn’t be better for after a day on the <a data-udi="umb://document/f7e065ba2a3d40d7893ad1b116880496" href="/{localLink:umb://document/f7e065ba2a3d40d7893ad1b116880496}" title="The Dolomites">Dolomite</a> walking and cycling trails.</p>
<h2>Cosy interiors and comfort food</h2>
<p>The rest of the hotel feels modern with a really cosy and quirky style. We love the rooms with their faux fur throws, alabaster stag heads and pine floors. Each one is styled differently with intricate wallpapers and little homely touches. They’ve all got private balconies with stunning views of the mountains. We love the food here - the restaurant takes guests on an Alpine culinary journey and they only use ingredients from the South Tyrol region. The wines are all from the hotel's own wine cellar and have been carefully chosen by the family.</p>]]></description>
